headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter scored 27 points, hitting seven 3-pointers, to help the Sacramento Kings win for the first time this season with a 119-113 victory over the Miami Heat on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings outlast Heat 119-113, win first game of Mike Brown era

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — The Charlotte Hornets were coming off a 20-point road loss to the Orlando Magic, playing on the second night of a back-to-back and without their starting front court of LaMelo Ball and Terry Rozier.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets spoil Curry's homecoming again, beat Warriors in OT

headlines.description: — Rookie Bennedict Mathurin scored a career-high 32 points, Tyrese Haliburton added 26 and the Indiana Pacers beat the Brooklyn Nets 125-116 on Saturday night.
— Joel Embiid scored 25 points and made a tiebreaking 3-pointer to help the Philadelphia 76ers squeeze by the Chicago Bulls 114-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 25, hits big 3 as 76ers beat Bulls 114-109

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo and Jrue Holiday each scored 34 points as the Milwaukee Bucks responded after falling behind in the fourth quarter to beat the Atlanta Hawks 123-115 on Saturday night and remain unbeaten.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks outlast Hawks 123-115 to maintain perfect record

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 38 points, and Oklahoma City erased an eight-point deficit in the final two minutes of regulation in a 117-111 overtime victory against the Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Thunder overtake Mavs for 117-111 OT win

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen and Kelly Olynyk each scored 23 points, including a pair of late 3-pointers, to lift the Utah Jazz to a 124-123 win over the Memphis Grizzlies, who were playing without Ja Morant.
